p2
VAnniversary fete
p3
sVnews
p4
VShri Vigneshwara Cultural Academy, Ramapuram, celebrated its fourth anniversary on March 15 at Dr. Vimala Convent, Nesapakkam. On the occasion, titles were conferred on veteran musicians T.K. Murthy (&#8216;Nandhi Nadha Nipuna&#8217;) and Thanjavur Sankara Iyer (&#8216;Sahitya Pitamahar&#8217;). Up and coming singer V. Deepika, a disciple of Sudha Ragunathan, was awarded a certificate of merit for her recent successful tour of the U.S.A. Natarajan, former director, Doordarshan Chennai, N. Murali of Sri Krishna Sweets, the local panchayat president and councillor and other dignitaries graced the occasion.Neyveli R. Santhanagopalan, president of the academy, welcomed the gathering.N. Murali announced two awards for those who render the Vishnu Sahasranamam as sung by M. S. Subbulakshmi, and Skanda Sashtikavacham as rendered by Soolamangalam Sisters. They will be given away at the next annual day fete. Mr. Murali also distributed certificates to members of the ladies wing of the academy, who had completed the one-year course on Anusha puja.The day ended with a soulful Carnatic recital by Neyveli Santhanagopalan who was accompanied by T.K. Murthy on the mridangam, Delhi Sundararajan on the violin and R. Guruprasad on the ghatam.
